We recommended that:
a) Municipal Accountant exert her best effort to gather documents relative to the fund transfers and further review the aging of trust funds to identify the dormant accounts of unutilized balances;
b) Municipal Accountant to ascertain the implemented fund transfers and effect full liquidation of accounts to the source agencies, and draw necessary journal entry thereof;
c) Municipal Accountant to disclose in the notes to financial statements the aging of payables for the Due to NGAs, GOCCs, and LGUs accounts;
d) Municipal Treasurer to refund the unused fund transfer balances with identified source agencies, or seek their written approval that the balance may be utilized for other certain purposes;
e) Concerned Municipal officials to effect the implementation of projects under the trust fund for the purpose they were established; and
f) Municipal Accountant to reclassify from Due to LGUs to Customers’ Deposit account the guaranty deposits for the market stalls.

