We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct the Municipal Accountant:

To draw a journal entry voucher to adjust the Construction in Progress (CIP) and Construction Materials Inventory accounts amounting to ₱15.790 million and ₱31.742 million respectively; 

Coordinate with the Municipal Engineering Office on the status of physical accomplishments of other development or infrastructure projects of the Municipality and adjust the CIP and Inventory accounts equivalent to the amount reflective of their actual statuses; 


Henceforth, record the purchase of construction materials to the Construction Materials Inventory in accordance with Section 114 of Volume I of the New Government Accounting System Manual and COA Circular No. 2015-009; and

Meantime the full repair of the access road in Barangay Calicuang is not practicable and the rehabilitation of Monfort Bridge will take quite some time, we suggest that the LGU find ways to prevent further deterioration of the subject road.

