Recommendations
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Inventory Committee, with the assistance of the Municipal Accountant and Supply Officer In-Charge to:
Conduct the annual physical count of all the property, plant and equipment acquired by the municipality during the year in order to update the RPCPPE;
Prepare the RPCPPE and submit to the Auditor concerned for validation, as the same should be submitted not later than January 31 of each year;
Maintain the prescribed stock cards/property cards and (SLC)/(PPELC), and reconcile the same with the RPCPPE to establish the correct amount of the PPE in the financial statements.
The aforementioned audit observation was communicated to management thru Audit Observation Memorandum No. 2018-008 dated February 26, 2018.

We continue to recommend that the Municipal Mayor direct the Inventory Committee, Municipal Accountant and GSO or Municipal Treasurer to:

Continue the conduct of the annual physical count of all the property, plant and equipment owned by the Municipality to update the RPCPPE to the current calendar year;
Prepare promptly the Report on the Physical Count of PPE (RPCPPE) and submit to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year;
Maintain the prescribed stock cards/property cards and (SLC)/(PPELC), and reconcile it with the RPCPPE to establish the correct amount of the PPE in the financial statements

