The aforementioned audit observation was communicated to management thru Audit Observation Memorandum No. 2016-007 dated February 22, 2017.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the Inventory Committee to:

Conduct the annual physical count of all the property, plant and equipment owned by the Municipality;
Prepare promptly the Report on the Physical Count of PPE;
Submit religiously the RPCPPE to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year.



We also recommend that the GSO-Designate and Municipal Accountant maintain the prescribed PPELC and reconcile it with the RPCPPE to establish the correct amount of the PPE in the financial statements.
